91
00:08:31,583 --> 00:08:34,333
- Alastor: SHANA, YOU WERE GOING
TO ASK ABOUT THAT, WEREN'T YOU?

92
00:08:35,083 --> 00:08:36,916
- UH, YEAH.

93
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:39,791
- A TRIVIAL REASON TO
POSTPONE ITS DESTRUCTION.

94
00:08:39,875 --> 00:08:42,583
- Alastor: YOU CANNOT
ASSUME THIS IS TRIVIAL.

95
00:08:42,666 --> 00:08:45,750
THIS MYSTES HAS AIDED US ON A
NUMBER OF OCCASIONS

96
00:08:45,833 --> 00:08:47,333
WITH HIS INSIGHT.

97
00:08:47,416 --> 00:08:50,416
- THAT'S RIGHT. HE HELPED US
IN THE LAST BATTLE.

98
00:08:50,500 --> 00:08:53,083
I THINK IT WOULD BE WISE
TO HEAR IT.

99
00:08:53,166 --> 00:08:55,625
WHAT THE MYSTES SAYS.

100
00:08:55,708 --> 00:08:57,666
- WHAT THE MYSTES SAYS.

101
00:09:02,125 --> 00:09:05,458
- THAT LOOK ON HER FACE.
IS IT THAT IMPORTANT?

102
00:09:17,333 --> 00:09:19,750
IF YOU TWO FEEL THIS
STRONGLY ABOUT IT,

103
00:09:19,833 --> 00:09:22,333
THEN I GUESS THERE MUST BE
SOME VALUE, INDEED,

104
00:09:22,416 --> 00:09:23,833
IN KEEPING THE MYSTES AROUND.

105
00:09:26,666 --> 00:09:30,208
I WILL POSTPONE DESTROYING
IT JUST THIS ONE TIME.

106
00:09:30,291 --> 00:09:31,333
- Tiamat: ACKNOWLEDGED.

107
00:09:32,000 --> 00:09:33,083
- WIRHELMINA.

108
00:09:38,500 --> 00:09:39,958
- INDEED I BELIEVE YOU.

109
00:09:41,625 --> 00:09:45,208
I INDEED DO NOT WISH TO
LOSE HOPE IN YOU.

110
00:09:55,000 --> 00:09:57,166
- SO, WHAT I WAS TRYING
TO TELL YOU...

111
00:09:58,416 --> 00:10:00,625
THE CITY'S REMAINING
BIRD ORNAMENTS...

112
00:10:00,708 --> 00:10:02,625
I WAS WONDERING IF
THEY'RE STILL SAFE.

113
00:10:02,708 --> 00:10:04,833
- Shana: Hmm?

114
00:10:04,916 --> 00:10:08,458
THAT DENIZEN YESTERDAY DIDN'T
TURN ALL OF THEM INTO RINNES.

115
00:10:08,541 --> 00:10:11,458
HE REALLY HAD NO USE FOR THEM?

116
00:10:11,541 --> 00:10:13,041
